==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Retrospective
<hw>Re`tro*spec"tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧trospectif</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Looking
backward; contemplating things past; -- opposed to
<ant>prospective</ant>; <as>as, a <ex>retrospective</ex>
view</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The sage, with <qex>retrospective</qex> eye.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having reference to what is past; affecting things
past; retroactive; <as>as, a <ex>retrospective</ex> law</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Inflicting death by a <qex>retrospective</qex> enactment.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Retrospectively</ent>⟦br⟧
